label.value: Oral Cavity Carcinoma

value.value: A carcinoma arising in the oral cavity.  Most oral cavity carcinomas are squamous cell carcinomas of the tongue, buccal mucosa, or gums.  Less frequent morphologic variants include mucoepidermoid carcinoma and adenocarcinoma.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with tumor invading through muscularis propria into subserosa or into mesoappendix. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with tumor penetrating visceral peritoneum including mucinous peritoneal tumor within the right lower quadrant and/or directly invading other organs or structures.  Direct invasion in T4 includes invasion of other segments of the colorectum by way of the serosa, e.g., invasion of ileum.  Tumor that is adherent to other organs or structures grossly is classified cT4b.  However, if no tumor is present in the adhesion microscopically, the classification should be pT1-3 depending on the anatomical depth of wall invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with tumor penetrating visceral peritoneum including mucinous peritoneal tumor within the right lower quadrant. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with tumor directly invading other organs or structures.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma without regional lymph node metastasis.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with metastasis in four or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for appendiceal carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Malignant Mastocytosis

value.value: A group of malignant mast cell disorders including aggressive systemic mastocytosis, mast cell leukemia, mast cell sarcoma, and systemic mastocytosis with an associated myeloid neoplasm. Individuals with advanced systemic mastocytosis have a reduced life expectancy, with median survival measured in months to years.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with intraperitoneal metastasis beyond the right lower quadrant, including pseudomyxoma peritonei. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with nonperitoneal metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Clinical assessment is based on medical history, physical examination, and imaging. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with intraperitoneal metastasis beyond the right lower quadrant, including pseudomyxoma peritonei. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoma cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoma with nonperitoneal metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Annotation Type

value.value: Defines the type of annotation (e.g., direct, mapped, transitive closure).

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Appendiceal carcinoids are usually staged after laparoscopic or open surgical exploration of the abdomen (often for appendicitis) and pathologic examination of the resected specimen.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor 1 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor more than 1 cm but not more than 2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor more than 2 cm but not more than 4 cm or with extension to the cecum.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor more than 4 cm or with extension to the ileum. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ureter Carcinoma

value.value: A carcinoma of the ureter.  The majority of ureter carcinomas are transitional cell and less frequently squamous cell carcinomas or adenocarcinomas.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with tumor directly invading other adjacent organs or structures, e.g., abdominal wall and skeletal muscle.  Penetration of the mesoappendix does not seem to be as important a prognostic factor as the size of the primary tumor and is not separately categorized. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid without regional lymph node metastasis.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for appendiceal carcinoid. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Clinical assessment is based on medical history, physical examination, and imaging.  Determination of elevated urinary 5-HIAA may indicate liver metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of appendiceal carcinoid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Malignant Lymphoma Centroblastic, Follicular

value.value: An antiquated term that refers to a follicular non-Hodgkin lymphoma composed predominantly of large B-lymphocytes.

label.value: Appendiceal Carcinoid cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Appendiceal carcinoid with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Colorectal Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Sarcomas, lymphomas, and carcinoid tumors of the large intestine are not included in this classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Colorectal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Most cancers of the colon and many cancers of the rectum are pathologically staged after surgical exploration of the abdomen, cancer-directed surgical resection, and pathologic examination of the resected specimen.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Colorectal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Colorectal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Colorectal cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial or invasion of lamina propria.  Note: Tis includes cancer cells confined within the glandular basement membrane (intraepithelial) or mucosal lamina propria (intramucosal) with no extension through the muscularis mucosae into the submucosa. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Colorectal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Colorectal cancer with invasion through the muscularis propria into pericolorectal tissues. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
